zipkin provides how one request is going through the entire distributed system
while micrometer gives you bird eye view of entire system like aggregated metric information

In Spring Boot 3.x, you typically had to add dependencies like:
spring-boot-starter-actuator
micrometer-tracing-bridge-brave
zipkin-reporter-brave

but In Spring Boot 4.x, the Spring team introduced the higher-level spring-boot-starter-zipkin
starter so that users don't need to know or manage the individual tracing libraries.
so we only need to add below dependency
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-zipkin</artifactId>
</dependency>

now as in jobms we are just using feign so we need to add a dependency for micrometer
<dependency>
    <groupId>io.github.openfeign</groupId>
    <artifactId>feign-micrometer</artifactId>
</dependency>
so that it can trace the data for interservice communication for feign client related queries.
